                            <comment id="409833" author="adilger" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2024 22:12:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was a bug in the patch being tested, unrelated to the test itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="385901" author="adilger" created="Thu, 14 Sep 2023 01:54:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like this failure has only been hit recently by this one patch, excluding large groups of failures from specific patches, or one individual failure that happened after a number of previous subtests have also failed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given the nature of the patch, which is modifying the Object Index used to look up files, there is a good chance that the subtest failure is a regression introduced by the patch itself.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
